HEADWORD: Schene
<hw>Schene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>schoenus</ets>, Gr. <?/ a rush, a reed, a land measure: cf. F.
<ets>sch⟦egrave⟧ne</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Antiq.)</fld> <def>An Egyptian or
Persian measure of length, varying from thirty-two to sixty
stadia.</def>⟦br⟧
